["The British Columbia Federation of Labour (BCFED) is a central organization for organized labour in British Columbia, Canada. It was founded in 1910 and claims to have a membership of 500,000, with 1,200 local and union sections.[1] The BCFED is the provincial affiliate of the Canadian Labour Congress and the umbrella organization for organized labour in British Columbia.","This British Columbia-related article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it.","This article related to a North American labor union or trade union is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]